cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.WEB, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper analyzes the usage and discovery of the Internet Archive's Wayback Machine, which is a web archiving and retrieval system. The paper uses web access logs to study user behavior and the links to the Wayback Machine. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.WEB (Web Technologies). The paper also discusses the preservation of cultural heritage and the challenges of web archiving, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
